WHAT THREE ADVICE WOULD YOU GIVE TO SOMEONE WHO IS JUST STARTING OUT AS A WRITER?

Don’t start because you want to become rich because you won’t. Seek to find pleasure in what you write and if you fall in love with it, you will write constantly and work really hard. If you don’t think it is really for you, don’t waste your time or money. Research subjects and stories but then it is your own personality that will make you write an interesting story.

WHAT EVENTS OR WORKSHOPS DO YOU OFFER WRITERS TO HELP THEM BECOME A WRITER?

Events in the UK that will talk about mental health and women issues. I really want to spread the word and help people and share with them my experiences.

I speak of my life, my pain and my suffering in a way that makes you feel what I felt. I tell you of my journey like a story with never ending hope.

ANYTHING ELSE YOU WOULD LIKE TO SHARE?

I am going to the Manhattan Book Fair this year with my novel ‘Chasing Cynthia’. I am really excited to see and share my work with people from all over the world.
